init_text: You're Barack Obama. 4 years into your retirement, you awake to find a letter with no return address on your bedside table. It reads "I hope you've had a chance to relax Barack...but pack your bags and call the number below. It's time to start the real job." Signed simply, "JFK."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You call the number and the voice on the other end says "Welcome back Mr. President.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "But I'm just a civilian now," says Obama.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "You're a President again, and you've got a country to run."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "The United States of America, of course," says JFK.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "Well, there's me, of course," says JFK.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "So you're a miniature golf course?" asks Obama.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I'm actually a golf course that's been miniaturized."
